Method Detail

getAirportsWithinRadius

SortedSet<AirportDistance> getAirportsWithinRadius(LatLng position,
                                                   double radius,
                                                   int minRank)
                                                   throws InterruptedException
Returns airports within radius meters of position.

The airport ranks are at least minRank.
Results are sorted in order of increasing distance from position.

Parameters:
position - Center of radius search
radius - Radius of search [meters]
minRank - Minimum airport rank to return
Throws:
InterruptedException

getAirportsInRectangle

Collection<Airport> getAirportsInRectangle(LatLngRect area,
                                           int minRank)
                                           throws InterruptedException
Returns airports in area.

The returned collection is in fact a set: no airport can be included more than once. The return value is kept as a Collection for performance reasons: membership tests in Set implementations can be unecessarily costly.

Parameters:
area - Area of search
minRank - Minimum airport rank to return
Throws:
InterruptedException

open

void open()
Prepares this object for future calls.

This method must be called prior to any other call

close

void close()
Closes this object.

This method must be called after all other calls. No other method should be called on this without calling open() first.
